          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "2021 sees Pokémon reach its 25th annual milestone. It’s a franchise that has defined generations due to its overwhelming presence and solid gameplay accessible to players of all ages. To celebrate, we have the remakes of the fourth generation of the mainline Pokémon entries with ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Pokémon Brilliant Diamond",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Pokémon Shining Pearl",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", a point in the franchise that marked the DS era of games and was a slight refresh to the series after a popularity decline from Generation three. So dive into the nostalgia and get ready for a challenge as Cynthia prepares her Garchomp and destroys my Nuzlocke run of the game.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TUOlZBxdrTA",
