            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " feel like one step forward in some aspects but one step backwards in others as the legitimate challenge in the Elite 4 was a welcome change but the lack of additional content to a remake has the game feel a bit empty. In saying that though, this is a great way for newer players to experience the fourth generation without having to resort to expensive or illegal methods. Overall, these remakes are solid experiences for players to enjoy with options of self imposed challenge runs for more seasoned Pokémon enthusiasts, which becomes more accessible for me thanks to the Sinnoh Grand Underground as I go and start my mono-fire type run.",
